<br>
Depends on your stat stackup - but a general rule is this:<br>
<br>
Assume 15 combines per level advanced<br>
<br>
Your at 130 - so you are at what I refer to as Boot Stage - the last of the single sheet items that can be combined to make an item.  So you need a boot mold (assume about 1PP and a Sheet of Metal - about 1.2PP) so 2.2PP per combine and assume you lose 20% of the value on resale - you need 5 points at 15 tries per point - 75 combines.  Thats 75 combines*2.2PP/combine*0.20 = 33 PP to reach 135.  You might get better return value if you're charismatic.<br>
<br>
Now to get from 135 to 160 (where I am) I recommend gauntlets (trivial at 168 and mold is only 3GP or so).  Its a two sheeter - so figure about 2.4 PP in metal and 3GP in the mold for 2.7 PP per attempt.  Thats 25 points @ 15 combines per point @ 2.7PP per combine @ 0.4 = 400PP ish.  Sadly - that actually seems right.  SO about 600 PP to get to the 160 level from 135.<br>
<br>
To get to 175 you first make boots to 168 and then cloaks to 175 - but really you can start making other things - but boots and cloaks are cheapest - components cost about 4.2PP.  <br>
<br>
8 points @ 15combines/point @ 2.7 PP/combine@0.2= 65 PP to 168.<br>
<br>
7 points @ 15combines/point @ 4.2 PP/combine@0.2 = 88 PP to 175.<br>
<br>
No wonder I'm poor - heh<br>
<br>
So total is about 650PP to level 175 from level 130.  That sounds right sadly.  Getting to 130 is cheap - usually costs about 100 PP - if you can't find someone to buy your wares as you make them, you can burn cash fast.  In going from 144-160 I burned 250PP easily - and that was my cash reserve not counting sales of banded to low levels.<br>
<br>
All of the above changes if you are very intelligent/wise and cute.  Norrath is a harsh world for a homely dwarf.<br>
<br>
